Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} from the fridge to bring them up to room temperature.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @lime{1/2}.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the tomato, a squeeze of lime juice, drizzle of @olive oil{} and the @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

Transfer the steaks to a #plate{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} on both sides.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When the chips have 10 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side. Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want them medium-rare.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a plate, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

== Sauce ==

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat.

Add the @water for the sauce{50%ml}, @sambal paste{30%g} (add less if you prefer things milder), @miso paste{15%g} and @honey{15%g} to the pan.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir to combine, bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Stir through the @butter{20%g} until melted. Add a squeeze of lime juice.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, add the @wild rocket{20%g} to bowl of tomatoes and toss to coat in the dressing.

Slice the steaks widthways and transfer to your plates. Spoon over the miso honey glaze.

Serve the sweet potato chips and tomato salad alongside. Enjoy!